# MJML Block Partial Structure Rules

## 1. Basic Container Structure
- Always start with an HTML comment describing the block's purpose
- Use `<mj-column>` as the root container
- Add appropriate CSS classes for dark mode and mobile responsiveness:
  ```mjml
  css-class="block-container light-section dark-mode-section"
  ```

## 2. Padding & Spacing
- Root sections: `padding="20px"`
- Inner columns: `padding="0"` or `padding="20px"` depending on design
- Content elements (text, buttons): Use consistent padding
  - Top/bottom padding: 10px
  - Side padding: 0px or 20px

## 3. Typography System
### Headers
```mjml
<mj-text
  font-family="'Questa Slab', Arvo, Rockwell, Verdana, Arial, sans-serif"
  font-weight="bold"
  font-size="14px"
  color="#000000"
>
```

### Body Text
```mjml
<mj-text
  font-family="'Ringside', Roboto, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif"
  font-size="14px"
  color="#000000"
>
```

## 4. Column Layout Rules
- Single column: Use full width
- Two columns: 
  - Image column: `width="45%"`
  - Content column: `width="55%"`
- Always add `css-class="mobile-stack-column"` for responsive design

## 5. Images
```mjml
<mj-image
  padding="0"
  fluid-on-mobile="true"
  css-class="content-image"
  src="https://ncd.test.technolutions.net/www/images/unc_brdmk_clr.png"
  align="left"
/>
```

## 6. CTA Buttons
```mjml
<mj-button
  background-color="#013C65"
  color="#FFFFFF"
  font-family="'Ringside', Roboto, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif"
  font-weight="bold"
  font-size="14px"
  align="center"
  border-radius="4px"
>
```

## 7. Dark Mode Support
- Add these classes to sections that need dark mode:
  - `dark-mode-section`: For background color switching
  - `dark-mode-text`: For text color switching
  - `dark-bg-link`: For link color adaptation

## 8. Mobile Responsiveness
Required classes:
- `mobile-stack-column`: For columns that should stack on mobile
- `mobile-center`: For content that should center align on mobile
- `content-image`: For images that need mobile optimization

## 9. Background Colors
Common background colors:
- White (default): No background color specified
- Blue: `#013C65`
- Gold: `#F6B000`
- Grey: `#EBEBEB`

## 10. File Naming Convention
- Prefix: Always use `block-`
- Descriptive name: Describe the main purpose
- Example: `block-body-content-white.mjml`

## 11. Class Usage Guidelines
### mj-class vs css-class
- `mj-class`: 
  - Applied directly to the MJML element as inline styles
  - Use for core styling that must work in all email clients
  - Ideal for font properties, colors, and spacing
  - Example:
    ```mjml
    <mj-class name="header" 
      font-size="24px" 
      color="#013C65" 
      padding="10px" />
    ```

- `css-class`:
  - Applied to the outer wrapper element in generated HTML
  - Use for responsive design and progressive enhancement
  - Required for dark mode and mobile adaptations
  - When styling, target inner elements if needed:
    ```css
    .dark-mode-text div {
      color: #ffffff !important;
    }
    ```

### Best Practices
- Use `mj-class` for:
  - Typography base styles
  - Colors that must work everywhere
  - Consistent spacing
  - Core layout properties

- Use `css-class` for:
  - Dark mode toggles
  - Mobile responsiveness
  - Progressive enhancements
  - Dynamic styling that's okay to fail gracefully
